                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/60.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18T19:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 16, 5 p.m. General Natera, Governor of Zacatecas, at present in
                    Monterey disclaims any knowledge of death and persecution of Christian Brothers.
                    States that Villa would know of the facts <pb facs="0988" n="872"
                        xml:id="pg_872"/> in the case. Have made verbal and written representation
                    to Governor Carranza in the matter. Welfare of Christian Brothers at Saltillo
                    reported to Department yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
